=== Expected Outcomes

If periodization shows benefit:
    - Establishes structured deload cycles as evidence-based option for selected patients
    - Provides clear protocol for implementation
    - Opens research into optimal cycle length and deload depth
If no benefit or harm observed:
    - Standard flexible pacing remains evidence-based default
    - May indicate that pre-planned cycles cannot accommodate ME/CFS variability
    - Redirects focus to real-time adaptive pacing strategies
